preText:
9.40pm So the first ball of the chase is to be bowled more than 20 minutes after the KKR innings ended. Umesh has the new ball, and he will bowl to Kohli.

KKR bring in Suyash Sharma for Iyer as Impact Sub.

Kohli and du Plessis, fresh from their stand of 148 against MI, walk out in pursuit of 205. Eden Gardens has been yelling Kohli and RCB's chants in the build-up to this game, so let's see who they root for if this gets tense.

9.30pm Hello, everyone. I'm sure a lot of us were left wondering if that was it for KKR at 89 for 5, especially with only the bowlers to follow. But now we have an entirely different game going on: RCB's required rate starts from above ten an over; however, there are short boundaries around, and the dew could play a role too. Meanwhile, Sampath just pings saying that KKR's run rate of 13.53 after the fall of the fifth wicket today is the second-highest in IPL history when a team has been five down for less than a hundred, and the sixth-wicket pair has faced at least 30 balls.

text: very good catch by Varun! He ended up where an imaginary midwicket fielder would have been, diving forward to complete the catch. There were two others rushing towards the ball, but Varun kept his eyes on it, not getting distracted by Gurbaz reaching so close to his left. The ball was flirted up right into the clouds, as Deep went heaving at this full ball, only to get a top edge. KKR win by 81 runs
postText:
A one-sided game in what was Eden Gardens' first IPL match in four years. KKR cruised to an 81-run win after hitting back from a position where everyone except Thakur had given up. Have a read of Monga's report from today's play, which included RCB collapsing from 44 for 0 to 61 for 5. That's it from us tonight, as this is Himanshu signing off on behalf of Raghav, Thilak and Monga! Good night.

Shardul Thakur is the Player of the Match for his match-turning 68 off 29: "Even I don't know where it came from! Looking at the scorecard, everyone would have said we were struggling. But your subconscious mind takes over. You also have to have skills to do that at the higher level, but we also work hard in the nets. Coaching staff do the throwdowns, and give us the option of range-hitting. And you know the pitches; they always suit the batsmen, don't they? Suyash bowled exceptionally well, and we know the quality Sunil and Varun have. They have fun, take wickets. This was a perfect day"

KKR captain Nitish Rana: "If you look at the last match, there were positives; we were in the game even after seven down. Even today, we collapsed, and credit to Gurbaz. And it was an unbelievable innings from Shardul Thakur! People will talk about Shardul, but Rinku held one end up, as we had planned. We had always planned not to give RCB batters pace in the middle overs. Suyash, playing his first match, bowled brilliant balls to such batters. Not even we have got to know him so far! He backs himself. It was always our plan to add him if we needed a third spinner."

Time for the presentations

Shrikant : "23 extras by RCB was another crime committed "

KKR coach Chandrakant Pandit: "It's a good win. Boys have shown the character. Looking at the initial stage, having lost wickets, and coming back to get 200-plus. We just expected the pitch to help the spinners. But you require enough runs. Shardul and Rinku counterattacked the opposition. We have seen him (Suyash) at trial matches. He is very quick in the air, and it's very tough to pick him. It's just the inexperience; but he showed a fighting attitude."

RCB captain Faf du Plessis after the loss: "We had it set up there in the 12th or 13th over... It was probably 20-25 runs too much. Shardul played well. Their legspinners got on top of us. It was still a good wicket... but the nature of mystery spinners is that they get wickets. They put the squeeze on us. We were pretty average with the bat. You learn lessons. Two or three days ago, you played brilliant cricket. It got away from us."

Afeef: "Shardul's knock will remain one of the best knocks when this season ends"

11.09pm Hardly a challenge here from the Royal Challengers. KKR were 89 for 5 in the 12th over of their innings - including having Russell back in the hut - but Thakur turned the screw thereon, and how! Strangely, only three KKR batters entered double figures, but you can imagine the impact they had as their side ended at 204. Add to that not one, not two, but three mystery spinners: four wickets for Varun, three for debutant Suyash and two for Narine, and that was it. Hang around for the presentation formalities.

text: stars with a length ball that started from outside off and came in. Flicked behind square leg for one
preText:
7.30pm Mayank Agarwal and Anmolpreet Singh are in the middle. Kyle Mayers, the specialist first-over bowler, will open the bowling. No slip - Thilak reminds me Mayers bowls inswing predominantly.

Gul: "Why was Abishek dropped? Is he also unwell? I dont see any other reason for dropping him :|" --- Think since they needed a keeper, they replaced Abhishek with Anmolpreet.

Prakash: "Finally some innovative use of the impact sub rule. SRH have kept all 3 options open( batter, allrounder or bowler) depending on match situation."

Amit: "Am I the only one confused here? SRH don't have a keeper, unless they sub Klassen" --- Anmolpreet Singh can sort of keep.

Chandan: "They will Substitute Klassen in place of Anmolpreet or Agarwal later in this innings...(that's the only logical way I see his inclusion as Substitute)" --- And if they need a batter for just one or two overs, they can bring in Jansen as well.

Hari: "So Naveen-ul-haq gets the cap but he is not there in the playing XI?" --- Yeah, a bit strange. Maybe he was in bat-first XI - just my guess. I don't think even that makes much sense.

Mannan: "I don't seem to comprehend this SRH lineup. Why use Klaasen as specialist keeper? This is just wastage of impact player rule. Klaasen should've been included in the first innings in the place of Natarajan and Natarajan should've been used as an impact sub for Anmolpreet" --- I think they will call up Klaasen if they collapse, else they get an extra bowler in Jansen or Farooqi in the second innings.

So after all that build-up, there's no de Kock. And SRH have only three overseas players in their XI. So expect one of Klaasen, Farooqi and Jansen to come in as an Impact Player at some stage.

Here are the playing XIs:

Sunrisers Hyderabad: 1 Mayank Agarwal, 2 Anmolpreet Singh (wk), 3 Rahul Tripathi, 4 Aiden Markram (capt), 5 Harry Brook, 6 Washington Sundar, 7 Abdul Samad, 8 Bhuvneshwar Kumar, 9 T Natarajan, 10 Umran Malik, 11 Adil Rashid
Substitues: Heinrich Klaasen, Fazalhaq Farooqi, Mayank Markande, Mayank Dagar, Marco Jansen

Lucknow Super Giants: 1 KL Rahul*, 2 KR Mayers, 3 DJ Hooda, 4 MP Stoinis, 5 N Pooran†, 6 R Shepherd, 7 KH Pandya, 8 A Mishra, 9 Yash Thakur, 10 JD Unadkat, 11 Ravi Bishnoi
Substitues: Ayush Badoni, Swapnil Singh, Daneil Sams, Prerak Mankad, Avesh Khan

7.00pm Sunrisers have won the toss and opted to bat first. "The wicket looks quite dry," says Markram. "Hopefully, we can put up a good total. Everyone seems in good spirits and full of energy. Since we are batting first, Anmolpreet Singh will start."

"Even during the last game I didn't expect it to be a high-scoring one," KL Rahul says. "We will assess the conditions and try to do our best. Wood is down with flu, so he misses out. Avesh injured himself in the last game, so he is taking a break."

6.55pm Pitch Report: We have got a black-soil pitch tonight, which means less pace and bounce as compared to the last game that was played on a red-soil pitch. We are not expecting much dew either, says Simon Katich. He says batting first could be the better option.

6.50pm Looks like LSG have handed caps to Romario Shepherd and Naveen-ul-Haq. I am guessing someone is not fit 100%. Heinrich Klaasen too seems to have got his SRH cap, which was more or less obvious. Does that mean Glenn Phillips sit out?

IPL Super Selec: "Sundar would love to see two lefties open. That would jumpstart his career after the injury hiatus"

6.45pm In the small window Mayers had before Quinton de Kock's arrival, he did everything he could to make it extremely hard for Lucknow Super Giants to drop him. Deivarayan Muthu charts his journey.

Play ESPNcricinfo's first AR-based game - just aim and hit the stumps.

You can follow the ball-by-ball commentary of the match in Hindi and Tamil too.

6.40pm Sunrisers too have their South African trio available. Aiden Markram will take over the captaincy from Bhuvneshwar Kumar. But will Heinrich Klaasen and Marco Jansen get a game straightaway? If yes, for whom do they come in for? While we wait for the toss, you can read our match preview here.

RajatMaheshwari: "The only option LSG have if they want to play QDK is to drop Stoinis...he hasn't gotten away in both the matches and hasn't bowled either. With contributions from Mayers and Pooran, I don't see it any other way!"

Tauqeer: "Very simple , drop Stoins and let Rahul bat at No 3. That would be the deadliest opening pair of this year's IPL."

6.30pm S16E10. It's Lucknow Super Giants taking on Sunrisers Hyderabad at Ekana Cricket Stadium. Both teams are coming off a defeat but have also been bolstered by the availability of their South Africans players. Quinton de Kock is back for LSG, and have given them a happy headache. Do they drop Mayers, who has smashed two half-centuries in two games. Or do they leave out one of Stoinis or Pooran? And if both de Kock and Mayers play, who should open? Do let us know what you think.

postText:
Ravi Bishnoi: It was a difficult wicket for batting and our bowlers did well. It's dicey score, but we will try to finish it quickly. I knew Brook will look to come down, so I slipped in a legbreak. Samad finished well for them but we will back ourselves to chase it down.

9.05pm So Samad's cameo of 21 off 10 means SRH have just crossed 120 on a slow, low, dying pitch. Krunal was the pick of the bowlers, picking up 3 for 18 from his four. Bishnoi was economical as well, conceding just 16 from his quota for the wicket of Brook. Mishra too chipped in with two towards the end. Can SRH make a contest out of it? Himanshu will be here in a bit to find out.

preText:
Bhuvi has the new ball. Slip for Mayers.

So Farooqi is SRH's Impact Sub for Tripathi. Most of us wondered if Markande would come in instead.

Ash: "9:20 pm? It's still 9:18!" --- I just travelled in time

9.20pm Hello, everyone. A pitch with barely any life in it - there is hardly any pace and bounce to play with - and SRH's spinners as much as Bhuvneshwar will be handy with their variations and cutters. This could be the season's first low-scoring thriller if SRH take it deep, and LSG flounder.
